y/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.toGlueL","doc":"The canonical map from `X` to the space obtained by gluing isometric subsets in `X` and `Y`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L485-L487","name":"Metric.instMetricSpaceGlueSpace","kind":"instance","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.instMetricSpaceGlueSpace","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L480-L481","name":"Metric.GlueSpace","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.GlueSpace","doc":"Given two isometric embeddings `Φ : Z → X` and `Ψ : Z → Y`, we define a\nspace  `GlueSpace hΦ hΨ` by identifying in `X ⊕ Y` the points `Φ x` and `Ψ x`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L470-L475","name":"Metric.gluePremetric","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.gluePremetric","doc":"Given two isometric embeddings `Φ : Z → X` and `Ψ : Z → Y`, we define a pseudo metric space\nstructure on `X ⊕ Y` by declaring that `Φ x` and `Ψ x` are at distance `0`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L443-L453","name":"Metric.Sigma.completeSpace","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.completeSpace","doc":"A disjoint union of complete metric spaces is complete. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L438-L439","name":"Metric.Sigma.isometry_mk","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.isometry_mk","doc":"The injection of a space in a disjoint union is an isometry "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L412-L428","name":"Metric.Sigma.metricSpace","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.metricSpace","doc":"A metric space structure on the disjoint union `Σ i, E i`.\nWe embed isometrically each factor, set the basepoints at distance 1, arbitrarily,\nand say that the distance from `a` to `b` is the sum of the distances of `a` and `b` to\ntheir respective basepoints, plus the distance 1 between the basepoints.\nSince there is an arbitrary choice in this construction, it is not an instance by default. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L383-L404","name":"Metric.Sigma.isOpen_iff","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.isOpen_iff","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L351-L380","name":"Metric.Sigma.dist_triangle","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.dist_triangle","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L345-L348","name":"Metric.Sigma.fst_eq_of_dist_lt_one","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.fst_eq_of_dist_lt_one","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L339-L342","name":"Metric.Sigma.one_le_dist_of_ne","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.one_le_dist_of_ne","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L334-L336","name":"Metric.Sigma.dist_ne","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.dist_ne","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L329-L330","name":"Metric.Sigma.dist_same","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.dist_same","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L322-L323","name":"Metric.Sigma.instDist","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.instDist","doc":"A `Dist` instance on the disjoint union `Σ i, E i`.\nWe embed isometrically each factor, set the basepoints at distance 1, arbitrarily,\nand say that the distance from `a` to `b` is the sum of the distances of `a` and `b` to\ntheir respective basepoints, plus the distance 1 between the basepoints.\nSince there is an arbitrary choice in this construction, it is not an instance by default. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L309-L314","name":"Metric.Sigma.dist","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sigma.dist","doc":"Distance on a disjoint union. There are many (noncanonical) ways to put a distance compatible\nwith each factor.\nWe choose a construction that works for unbounded spaces, but requires basepoints,\nchosen arbitrarily.\nWe embed isometrically each factor, set the basepoints at distance 1, arbitrarily,\nand say that the distance from `a` to `b` is the sum of the distances of `a` and `b` to\ntheir respective basepoints, plus the distance 1 between the basepoints.\nSince there is an arbitrary choice in this construction, it is not an instance by default. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L287-L288","name":"Metric.isometry_inr","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.isometry_inr","doc":"The right injection of a space in a disjoint union is an isometry "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L282-L283","name":"Metric.isometry_inl","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.isometry_inl","doc":"The left injection of a space in a disjoint union is an isometry "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L278-L278","name":"Metric.Sum.dist_eq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sum.dist_eq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L249-L273","name":"Metric.metricSpaceSum","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.metricSpaceSum","doc":"The distance on the disjoint union indeed defines a metric space. All the distance properties\nfollow from our choice of the distance. The harder work is to show that the uniform structure\ndefined by the distance coincides with the disjoint union uniform structure. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L226-L227","name":"Metric.Sum.one_le_dist_inr_inl","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sum.one_le_dist_inr_inl","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L221-L223","name":"Metric.Sum.one_le_dist_inl_inr","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sum.one_le_dist_inl_inr","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L211-L215","name":"Metric.Sum.dist_eq_glueDist","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sum.dist_eq_glueDist","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L204-L208","name":"Metric.Sum.dist","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.Sum.dist","doc":"Distance on a disjoint union. There are many (noncanonical) ways to put a distance compatible\nwith each factor.\nIf the two spaces are bounded, one can say for instance that each point in the first is at distance\n`diam X + diam Y + 1` of each point in the second.\nInstead, we choose a construction that works for unbounded spaces, but requires basepoints,\nchosen arbitrarily.\nWe embed isometrically each factor, set the basepoints at distance 1,\narbitrarily, and say that the distance from `a` to `b` is the sum of the distances of `a` and `b` to\ntheir respective basepoints, plus the distance 1 between the basepoints.\nSince there is an arbitrary choice in this construction, it is not an instance by default. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L168-L175","name":"Metric.glueMetricApprox","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.glueMetricApprox","doc":"Given two maps `Φ` and `Ψ` intro metric spaces `X` and `Y` such that the distances between\n`Φ p` and `Φ q`, and between `Ψ p` and `Ψ q`, coincide up to `2 ε` where `ε > 0`, one can almost\nglue the two spaces `X` and `Y` along the images of `Φ` and `Ψ`, so that `Φ p` and `Ψ p` are\nat distance `ε`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L111-L113","name":"Metric.le_glueDist_inr_inl","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.le_glueDist_inr_inl","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L107-L109","name":"Metric.le_glueDist_inl_inr","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.le_glueDist_inl_inr","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L100-L105","name":"Metric.glueDist_swap","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.glueDist_swap","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L81-L90","name":"Metric.glueDist_glued_points","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.glueDist_glued_points","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.lean#L70-L74","name":"Metric.glueDist","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Gluing.html#Metric.glueDist","doc":"Define a predistance on `X ⊕ Y`, for which `Φ p` and `Ψ p` are at distance `ε` "}]}